article.description: Anthony Lawrence threw for four touchdowns as San Diego remained undefeated in the Pioneer League, beating Drake 38-7 on Saturday.
article.headline: San Diego stays on top in Pioneer with 38-7 win over Drake
article.linkText: San Diego stays on top in Pioneer with 38-7 win over Drake
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Anthony Lawrence threw for four touchdowns as San Diego remained undefeated in the Pioneer League, beating Drake 38-7 on Saturday. Lawrence had 259 yards on 19-of-29 passing for the Toreros (5-1, 4-0). Brian Riley and Ross Dwelley caught two touchdowns apiece and Jonah Hodges ran for 112 yards. The Toreros led the Bulldogs (3-4, 2-2) throughout the game, beginning with Lawrence's 17-yard touchdown pass to Riley in the first quarter. Tevin Heyward ran for a score midway through the second and Lawrence followed with an 8-yard touchdown throw to Dwelley to make it 21-0 with 2:36 to go before the break. Patrick Murray kicked a 44-yard field goal to put San Diego up 24-0 at halftime. Drake's Drew Lauer prevented the shut-out with a 9-yard scoring run with 7:38 left in the game. Starting Bulldogs QB Grant Kraemer -- who was replaced in the fourth quarter -- had 116 yards passing and one interception.
